headline: Precious Metals Drop After Trump Posts About Greenland Deal
summary: Front-month gold futures finished at a new all-time high, but turned lower after President Trump posted on Truth Social that he had reached “the framework” of a deal with NATO Secretary General Mark Rutte over Greenland and the Arctic region. Silver futures also fell.

headline: Copper Supported by Commercial Hedging But Gains Capped by Trade Concerns
summary: Copper prices rose. Sucden Financial said data showed that speculative investors had trimmed long positions, while commercial participants remained active, providing steady support through hedging.

headline: Gold Likely to Be Supported by ‘Price-Insensitive’ Central Banks
summary: Gold is likely to have “enduring support” from sustained, largely price-insensitive demand from central banks looking to diversify their reserves, said T. Rowe Price’s Matt Bance.
